The paper focuses on robotic grasp detection using deep learning-based approaches, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image processing and detection suggests that the paper also belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The high accuracy achieved by the proposed method indicates the use of advanced machine learning techniques, such as deep learning, which aligns with the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE).
